    "biomarker_clinical_significance": {
        "clinical_significance": "Elevated inflammatory cytokines (IL-6, TNF-α, IL-1ra, sTNF-RII, neopterin) correlate with fatigue severity and serve as targets for anti-inflammatory interventions. Hemoglobin levels <12 g/dL directly contribute to fatigue, with correction improving outcomes. Cortisol dysregulation (altered diurnal rhythm) is addressed by corticosteroids. Genetic polymorphisms (e.g., IL-6 rs1800795) are associated with persistent fatigue. Biomarkers guide management of modifiable factors but lack standalone diagnostic specificity."
    },
